s, United Kingdom":"Monknash, Glamorgan, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"1195–":"1195–Deceased","1165–1203":"1165–1203","1183–Male":"1183–Deceased","1185–1219":"1185–1219","1185–Male":"1185–Deceased","1190–1238":"1190–1238","1195–Male":"1195–Deceased","1197–1219":"1197–1219","1199–Male":"1199–Deceased","1200–1246":"1200–1246","1199–Female":"1199–Deceased","1221–Female":"1221–Deceased","1160–1203":"1160–1203","1151–1219":"1151–1219","1190":"1190","1165":"1165","1197":"1197","1185":"1185","1195":"1195","1151":"1151","1183":"1183","1160":"1160","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1203":"1203","1224":"1224","1246":"1246","Abt 1221":"about 1221","1200":"1200","1221":"1221","1199":"1199","1219":"1219","Aldingham, Lancashire, England":"Aldingham, Lancashire, England","Mounton, Monknash, Glamorganshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Monknash, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Fleming","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["English: ethnic name for someone from Flanders, from Middle English <i>fleming</i>. The word reflects a Norman French form of Old French <i>flamanc</i> ‘Fleming’, from the stem <i>flam-</i> + the ancient Germanic suffix <i>-ing</i>. In the Middle Ages there was considerable commercial intercourse between England and the Netherlands, particularly in the wool trade, and many Flemish weavers and dyers settled in England. This surname is also common in south and east Scotland and in Ireland, where it is sometimes found in the Gaelicized form <b>Pléamonn</b>.","German: variant of   Flemming  , cognate with 1 above."],"variants":[{"name":"Flemings","meanings":["English: plural form of   Fleming  .","Americanized form of Flemish <b>Vleminckx</b>: patronymic from <b>Vleminck</b>, an ethnic name for someone from Flanders, Middle Dutch <i>vleminc</i>."]},{"name":"Flanders","meanings":["English: ethnic name from Middle English <i>Fla(u)ndres</i> ‘Flanders’, denoting someone from Flanders, a historical region covering parts of modern-day Belgium, France, and the Netherlands. Compare   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Fleeman","meanings":["English: variant of   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Flemming","meanings":["German: ethnic name for someone from Flanders, Middle High German <i>vlaeminc</i>. People from Flanders spread throughout Germany, as well as England, in the Middle Ages as clothmakers and dyers.","English: variant of   Fleming  ."]},{"name":"Flamenco","meanings":["Spanish: ethnic name from <i>flamenco</i> ‘Fleming, Flemish person’ (see   Fleming  )."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705187,"age":20,"year":"1215","julianDay":2164830,"title":"Magna Carta","description":"King John of England agreed to a charter of rights called the Magna Carta. The document was originally drafted by the Archbishop of Canterbury to establish peace between King John and a group of rebel barons. The Magna Carta was completed in 1215 and is now considered to be one of the greatest constitutional documents of all time.","url":"https://www.nationalarchives.gov.uk/education/medieval/magna-carta/","urlTitle":"National Archives - Magna Carta","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705188,"age":29,"year":"1224","julianDay":2168117,"title":"France Declares War on England","description":"France declared war on England as Louis VIII of France attacked Poitou and northern Gascony.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705189,"age":64,"year":"1259","julianDay":2180901,"title":"100 Years of Conflict Between England and France Ends","description":"Treaty of Paris was signed on December 4, 1259, which ended 100 years of conflict between England and France.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Treaty_of_Paris_(1259)","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Treaty of Paris 1259","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Fleming was born in 1195, in Aldingham, Lancashire, England, his father, William le Fleming, was 36 and his mother, Ada de Workington, was 44. He had at least 1 daughter with Mrs. John Fleming."},"et":{"1195–":"1195–Surnud","1165–1203":"1165–1203","1183–Male":"1183–Surnud","1185–1219":"1185–1219","1185–Male":"1185–Surnud","1190–1238":"1190–1238","1195–Male":"1195–Surnud","1197–1219":"1197–1219","1199–Male":"1199–Surnud","1200–1246":"1200–1246","1199–Female":"1199–Surnud","1221–Female":"1221–Surnud","1160–1203":"1160–1203","1151–1219":"1151–1219","1190":"1190","1165":"1165","1197":"1197","1185":"1185","1195":"1195","1151":"1151","1183":"1183","1160":"1160","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1203":"1203","1224":"1224","1246":"1246","Abt 1221":"umbes 1221","1200":"1200","1221":"1221","1199":"1199","1219":"1219","Aldingham, Lancashire, England":"Aldingham, Lancashire, England","Mounton, Monknash, Glamorganshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Monknash, Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1195–":"1195–Kuollut","1165–1203":"1165–1203","1183–Male":"1183–Kuollut","1185–1219":"1185–1219","1185–Male":"1185–Kuollut","1190–1238":"1190–1238","1195–Male":"1195–Kuollut","1197–1219":"1197–1219","1199–Male":"1199–Kuollut","1200–1246":"1200–1246","1199–Female":"1199–Kuollut","1221–Female":"1221–Kuollut","1160–1203":"1160–1203","1151–1219":"1151–1219","1190":"1190","1165":"1165","1197":"1197","1185":"1185","1195":"1195","1151":"1151","1183":"1183","1160":"1160","1238":"1238","1259":"1259","1215":"1215","1203":"1203","1224":"1224","1246":"1246","Abt 1221":"noin 1221","1200":"1200","1221":"1221","1199":"1199","1219":"1219","Aldingham, Lancashire, England":"Aldingham, Lancashire, England","Mounton, Monknash, Glamorganshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Monknash, Glamorgan, Wales, Yhdisty